  {"q": "What year is 2026 in the Chinese zodiac?", "a": "2026 is the Year of the Horse (马年). People born in Horse years (1942, 1954, 1966, 1978, 1990, 2002, 2014, 2026) are said to be energetic, independent, and adventurous."},
  {"q": "What is your Ben Ming Nian?", "a": "Your Ben Ming Nian (本命年) is when your zodiac year comes around again — every 12 years. It is considered an unlucky year because you are 'in conflict' with the Tai Sui (太岁) god. People wear red underwear and accessories throughout their Ben Ming Nian for protection."},
  {"q": "Which zodiac animals are most compatible?", "a": "Traditional compatibility follows a pattern: animals 4 positions apart are most compatible (forming 'trine' groups). The four trine groups are: Rat-Dragon-Monkey, Ox-Snake-Rooster, Tiger-Horse-Dog, and Rabbit-Goat-Pig. Animals 6 positions apart are considered incompatible."},
  {"q": "Why is the Dragon the most popular zodiac animal?", "a": "The Dragon (龙) is the only mythical animal in the zodiac and symbolizes power, strength, and good fortune in Chinese culture. Dragon years consistently see higher birth rates across China, Taiwan, and other Chinese communities as parents hope their children will inherit the Dragon's auspicious traits."}
